Product Requirements Document
AI Multi-Game Reinforcement Learning Agent Training and Arena Platform

1. Product Overview

The AI Multi-Game Reinforcement Learning Platform is a web-based system that enables users to design, train, evaluate, and deploy AI agents across multiple classic games using reinforcement learning algorithms. The platform supports Snake, Connect 4, Flappy Bird, Maze, and Pong, allowing users to configure agents with customizable hyperparameters and select from multiple RL algorithms including Q-Learning, SARSA, DQN, PPO, and A2C.

Users can train agents in real time, visualize training performance through live reward graphs, analyze decision-making via an explainability panel, and conduct Agent vs Agent competitions within an arena environment. The system provides persistent model storage, automated leaderboard updates, performance analytics, and downloadable PDF training reports.

The platform is delivered as a web application using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for the frontend, Flask for backend services, Flask-SocketIO for real-time communication, and PyTorch for AI model implementation.

Deadline: 3 April 2026.

2. Problem Statement

Reinforcement learning education and experimentation often require fragmented tools, manual configuration, and limited visualization capabilities. Most environments do not provide integrated model training, live explainability, agent-versus-agent evaluation, and performance analytics in a single unified system.

There is a need for a structured platform that enables users to:

* Train AI agents in different game environments
* Compare algorithm performance under controlled conditions
* Visualize training dynamics and model behavior
* Conduct competitive evaluations
* Generate structured reports for academic or research purposes

This platform addresses these gaps by providing a centralized, interactive reinforcement learning experimentation ecosystem.

