18. Risks and Mitigation

Risk: Training instability in deep RL algorithms.
Mitigation: Implement gradient clipping and reward normalization.

Risk: Long training times for complex games.
Mitigation: Episode limits and early stopping mechanisms.

Risk: WebSocket disconnections.
Mitigation: Automatic reconnection logic.

Risk: Model corruption.
Mitigation: Checkpoint-based saving and validation before storage.

