20. Conclusion

The AI Multi-Game Reinforcement Learning Platform is a comprehensive web-based environment designed for training, evaluating, and comparing reinforcement learning agents across multiple game environments. By integrating configurable algorithms, real-time visualization, explainability tools, arena-based competitions, and structured reporting, the platform provides a complete reinforcement learning experimentation ecosystem suitable for academic, research, and applied AI use cases. The architecture ensures modularity, scalability, and extensibility while maintaining robust performance and analytical capabilities.
